    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Temporary structures for protecting the open grave immediately prior to interment or immediately after burial; typically having the form of a canopy, ramada, or tent. For structures of similar form, a ramada or shed but intended to exist for months or years rather than hours or days, prefer "gravehouses." For raised, canopied structures under which the coffin or effigy of a deceased person lies or is carried in state, prefer "catafalques."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
